<p>Wednesday 1st August 1917</p>
<p>Very heavy rain so were cleaning harness all morning in our dugout.<br/>Guns very quiet.<br/>1.30pm ordered to harness up. 2pm left camp and went to sawmills at Reninghelst for timber. Roads very muddy and by the time I got back to camp (5pm) I was covered in mud.<br/>First rum issue.</p>
